That gradient isn't computed on the CPU -- the vertex colors are interpolated by the GPU's rasterizer, just like in any shader pipeline. You can do the same with points:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
That gradient isn't computed on the CPU -- the vertex colors are interpolated by the GPU's rasterizer, just like in any shader pipeline. You can do the same with points:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Sequence[GraphicsComplex[{{-1,-1}, {1,-1}, {1,1}}, Point[{1,2,3}], VertexColors->{{1,0,0}, {0,1,0}, {0,0,1}}], "Controls"->False, ImageSize->250] // Graphics

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
(*VB[*)(Graphics[GraphicsComplex[{{-1, -1}, {1, -1}, {1, 1}}, Point[{1, 2, 3}], VertexColors -> {{1, 0, 0}, {0, 1, 0}, {0, 0, 1}}], "Controls" -> False, ImageSize -> 250])(*,*)(*"1:eJx1UMsKwjAQjC9QEPwGv6XgAzxIC96jprqQdks2QvHTvehuQ7UNNodhZ/Y1m/UZ03yklKIpww7tNZ8ImzNsna7ucKGgrDpKgkVlTR0S0ngA8vm4y+DNr4FIl2WDukCwM2M4IpS+vySUSSeI/puRPqyhJQcn47ypE7ToKDL4Z5JqIUqq1s1g8lvR95DJzyVYeoeWmis22pKJjC442Bf6ZjJ4Gngx+wB+nFOa"*)(*]VB*)

